WHY BUY A CDTV?

"I decided to buy a Commodore CDTV because i want to improve the experience
i can get from my TV and my Hi-Fi system.I want be able to learn
interesting subjects like story,stranger languages and then i want to have
qualified experiences with musical applications.
I also want be able to see the new CDs with graphic and connect my
electronic keyboard to the CDTV to play my preferred music.More,all my
family can see discs on CDTV"



QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS.

Q. How much time a new title development requires?

A. Obviously depends on the matter of the title and on the quality and
   quantity of the original stuff.For example, the Grolier Encyclopedia
   needed relatively little time, thinking at the project aim: three months to
   trace more than 9 millions of words, many thousands of images and more
   than a hour of audio.
   This has been possible because all the elements was already available in
   electronic format.
   The work requires to draw and code an user interface,to convert the
   existing searching-engine and to test the results;in other conditions
   this work this work will have needed years of work.

Q. What is the CDTV?

A. The CDTV is one of the first systems of a new generation of consumer
   electronic products;it's a sophisticated CD audio and video player to
   be connected to the TV and to the Hi-Fi.
   The CDTV reads a new kind of CDs for personal and familiar entertainment
   for learning and entertainment programs.
   Audio CDs and CD+Graphic also are played with superb results.The choice of
   interesting informations,images and sounds is made with JUST an infra-red
   remote control.

Q. What's the meaning of "interactive"?

A. The CDTV is an interactive system because who uses it becomes active in
   the choice of what he wants to see or hear.Instead of passively look at
   a pre-defined spectacle,the user can choose the most important 
   arguments and deep at own liking.
   Interactive means,besides,involving and stimulating one's creativity to
   get new ways.

Q. How does it work?Is it easy to use?

A. Commodore designed the CDTV so to make it easy to use;in fact
   is sufficient connect the CDTV to the TV,then the audio cables to the
   right and left speakers of your Hi-Fi,and then insert the CD in the
   reader and follow the instructions that will appear on the TV.

Q. How much data can be stored in a CD?

A. The CDTV CDs can store more than 650 Megabytes of digital datas,which is
   pair to about 250.000 text pages and thousands of colour images.The storage
   of memorizable informations depends on the proportion between sound and
   moving or not images.

Q. What is the price of a CDTV

A. The public selling price,at the launch, is 1.300.000 (NFT:Italian) lires
   including remote control,caddy to protect the CDs,audio/video  connections
   cables and welcome disk.

Q. Why a caddy is needed?

A. Because those new CDs require a major precision in the header alignment
   from the laser compared to normal audio CDs and even the fingerprints
   may interfere in reading the datas.
   The caddy ensures protection and precision for reading mechanism.

Q. How much will the discs cost?

A. From 25 to 90 thousands (Italian) lires due to the content;obviously
   an encyclopedia will cost more than a recipe-book

Q. The CDTV can be transformed in a Amiga-like home computer?

A. Certainly yes, but being a consumer electronic product made to stay in the
   room where usually there is the TV and the Hi-Fi,we don't think that many
   people will expand the CDTV functions.
   Will be possible buy accessories like the trackball, a special remote
   control to put on the armchair where to connect one or two joysticks or a
   keyboard.

Q. Which discs will be available?

A. At the launch more than 40 titles will be available,with arguments from
   the medical dictionary to recipe-books,from astronomy treatise to the
   world atlas, from the science manuals, to art and culture ones.There will
   also be a big availability of CD+graphic.

Q. Which languages will be available for the titles?

A. This is the first product that allows to have multilingual versions of
   the same title on the same disk.This means lower prices for the consumer
   and the possibility to have the same title available at the same time in
   many countries.The first titles are in English version,but the developers
   are already working in the realization of titles in many languages;
   now 6 titles are available in Italian

Q. Which is the quality level of the audio side of the CDTV?

A. The CD audio is a 16 bit 8xoversampling,it means that it is a good player
   that will be the natural complement of your actual Hi-Fi system.If have
   in the past bought a CD player, you'll see that the CDTV will give you a
   better quality;moreover,the image on the screen will let you program
   more easily the track you want to hear.

Q. What's the difference between CDTV and Philips CD-I?

A. First of all,Commodore has already launched either the CDTV and the
   titles,Philips,hasn't!
   The CDTV is the result of advanced and proved technologies:
   an operative system,a CD-ROM drive and an infrared remote control.
   The product has been amply tested before the launch,the prices of the
   titles are acceptable and there is a big developers community who has
   hundreds of experience years on Commodore systems.

Q. Will CDTV have full-screen full motion video?

A. At this moment this possibility is limited to a screen portion,that,for
   the new interactive titles,satisfies any need,even the more creative one.
   The full motion video will be available in next future,when the 
   international standard for compression,in developing phase by MPEG,will be
   defined.Anyway,we don't think the full motion video to be essential,but
   to be a more feature.
   But when will be available,there will be no problems to make the CDTV
   compatible with the new needs.

Q. Does the CDTV support the MIDI Interface?

A. The CDTV is fully MIDI compatible and has a built-in in and out MIDI
   interface.
   Even the not musician expert can make his electronic keyboard play,for
   example,the preferred music,using  all the keyboard features.

Q. What is the personal memory card function?

A. Its usage is limited just by the user's inventive for the many
   applications of the programs.First of all it is portable,thus allows to
   bring everywhere a game status or points,preferences,a keyword to stop
   other's access etc...
   This board can be used to edit big information quantities to "block"
   part of the infomations.For example a database can be sold on a CD at
   120.000 lires; with a cost 30.000 with a personal memory card (part of a
   set of 5 ones) is possible to access a fifth of the informations.In this
   way a price demolition is got,and the user can buy just the interesting
   part of informations.
